---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import NavBar from "../components/NavBar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Board Foot Calculator. Learn how we handle your data — we don't collect, store, or share any personal information."
>
  <NavBar />

  <main class="bg-primary">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-8 py-16 sm:px-14 lg:px-24 lg:py-24">
      <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-secondary px-3 py-1 text-caption-mono font-mono uppercase tracking-wide text-muted">
        Legal
      </span>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-display-xl text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-body-md text-muted">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-body-md text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          Board Foot Calculator does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. The calculator runs entirely in your browser. No account creation or email addresses are required. Any data you enter stays on your device.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">2. Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
          Your project cut list, theme preference, language choice, and cookie consent status are saved in your browser's <code class="rounded bg-secondary px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-body-sm">localStorage</code>. This data never leaves your device and is never accessible to us. You can clear it at any time through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          With your consent (via the cookie banner), this site uses:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> &mdash; to display advertisements. AdSense uses cookies and web beacons to serve relevant ads and measure performance. Google may use the data collected to personalise ads across its network.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> &mdash; to understand site traffic patterns. Analytics collects anonymised data about page visits, browser type, and device type.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> &mdash; for typography. Font requests may log your IP address.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          These services are only loaded after you accept cookies via the cookie banner. If you decline, no Google scripts run.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">4. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This site uses minimal cookies for essential functionality and, with your consent, for advertising and analytics. Google AdSense may place cookies for frequency capping, aggregated ad reporting, and fraud prevention. You can manage your consent preferences using the cookie banner that appears on your first visit, or by clearing your browser's localStorage.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          You can learn more about how Google uses data at <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" class="text-accent-mustard underline decoration-accent-mustard/30 hover:decoration-accent-mustard" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How Google uses data when you use our partners' sites or apps</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">5. Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can accept or decline cookies via the cookie banner. Even after accepting, you can withdraw consent by clearing your browser's localStorage (which removes your cookie preference) or by using your browser's cookie controls to block third-party cookies. Your cut list data is stored separately and is not affected by cookie consent changes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">6. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or share any personal data because we do not collect it. Google may receive anonymised data through AdSense and Analytics as described in their privacy policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes, the "Last updated" date at the top will reflect the revision. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-primary mt-8">8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this privacy policy? Reach out through our <a href="/contact" class="text-accent-mustard underline decoration-accent-mustard/30 hover:decoration-accent-mustard">Contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
